2024-02-19

(to be determined)

Methods:

  1. Kinetic Protocol (15-minute span, 8 measurements total, reduction: mean)

    1. 230nm (sensitive to protein conformation) -> A230 is a valid and convenient structural probe to determine thermodynamic stability and unfolding kinetics of proteins with many potential applications.[1]
    2. 260nm (nucleic acid detection)
    3. 280nm (protein detection)
    4. 650nm (practical turbidity wavelength)
    5. 980nm (turbidity interferes with pathcheck protocol at 900-1000nm)

  2. Dilutions from 1x to 16x for all seven samples

    1. WFI H2O (baseline sample)
    2. FFB2 (baseline buffer)
    3. FFB2 + PS20 (0.005%, sample buffer)
    4. DP 0% (high presence of particulates)
    5. DP 0.001% (moderate presence of particulates)
    6. DP 0.005% (no particulates observed in aliquot)
    7. DI2 (turbidity detection, 14DEC2023)

  3. Kinetic Protocol performed at 5 temperatures (C) for thermal aggregate detection

    1. 25
    2. 35
    3. 45
    4. 55
    5. 65
